body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/458\n\n## Problem\n`pm claim`/`pm start-task` reject --assignee (unknown_option) while pm update accepts it; agents naturally model claiming as assigning and try --assignee first. The recovery message lists where --assignee IS valid (create, list, list-all) but never points to --author, the actual claim-identity flag — a failed mutation in the critical path.\n\n## Proposed fix\nEither accept --assignee as an alias for --author on claim/release/start-task/pause-task (documented equivalence), or keep the contract strict and make the recovery message for these commands say: use --author <agent> for claim identity; use pm update --assignee for assignee metadata. Alias preferred per never-block routing precedent (2026-05-28 agent-UX pass).\n\n## Definition of done\n--assignee on lifecycle ownership commands either works or produces a targeted recovery hint naming --author; spec covers both commands; contracts/docs updated. Related: GH-444 item (global author ergonomics), pm-gdi7 (error suggestions)."
